# UDO Rules — Accuracy Critical

## Source of Truth
`backend/udo/udo_rules.json` contains hand-verified rules from the Durham UDO. NEVER guess at zoning values. If a rule seems wrong, verify at `https://udo.durhamnc.gov/udo/`.

## Common Gotchas

### Small Lot Tier Restrictions
- RS-8 and RS-10 small lot option is ONLY available in the **Urban Tier**, not county-wide
- RS-20 NEVER allows small lot option
- RC, RS-M, RU-M, RU-5, RU-5(2) allow small lot in ANY tier

### Compound Zoning Codes
Parcel data may contain compound codes like `RS-10/PDR`, `RU-5 CU`, `RS-M OL`. Strip overlays to extract the base residential zone. Common suffixes to strip: `/PDR`, `CU`, `OL`, `HP`, `NP`.

### Flag Lot Rules
- Min pole width: 20 ft (proposed reduction to 12 ft not yet adopted)
- The front setback of the flag lot equals the **side yard** setback of the district
- Both resulting lots must independently meet ALL dimensional standards
- Cannot make the parent (front) lot nonconforming

### Lot Averaging
- Max 15% reduction in individual lot area
- Average across ALL lots in the subdivision must still meet minimum
- Does NOT allow exceeding max density

## Key Numbers to Memorize
| District | Conventional Min Lot | Small Lot Min |
|----------|---------------------|---------------|
| RS-20    | 20,000 sf           | N/A           |
| RS-10    | 10,000 sf           | 2,000 sf*     |
| RS-8     | 8,000 sf            | 2,000 sf*     |
| RS-M     | 5,000 sf            | 2,000 sf      |
| RU-5     | 5,000 sf            | 2,000 sf      |
| RU-M     | 3,500 sf            | 2,000 sf      |

*Urban Tier only
